WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:03.360
TOMMY: <i>if the Italians win,
they're not planning on leaving.</i>

00:03.440 --> 00:05.080
<i>They're coming
and there here to stay.</i>

00:05.280 --> 00:08.560
Intelligence services in London have
sent seven officers up to Birmingham.

00:08.640 --> 00:10.320
<i>At the top of their list
is Ada Thorne.</i>

00:10.960 --> 00:14.000
Alfie Solomons runs a fighter.
Says it's money for nothing.

00:14.280 --> 00:17.280
That there, is the Southern Counties
welterweight champion,

00:17.360 --> 00:18.480
Name the day, Mr Shelby.

00:19.640 --> 00:21.920
Stop drinking whisky.
Switch to stout.

00:22.200 --> 00:24.400
And then go and see a doctor
about that baby.

00:24.480 --> 00:26.440
POLLY: <i>Make sure Tommy
keeps that Friday free.</i>

00:26.520 --> 00:28.280
<i>Tell him I have an appointment for him.</i>

00:28.600 --> 00:31.320
You've agreed to give up Tommy
to save my life.

00:43.480 --> 00:47.880
<i># Take a little walk
to the edge of town</i>

00:47.960 --> 00:51.000
<i># Go across the tracks</i>

00:53.440 --> 00:58.640
<i># Where the viaduct looms
like a bird of doom</i>

00:58.720 --> 01:02.840
<i># As it shifts and cracks</i>

01:04.120 --> 01:09.360
<i># Where secrets lie in the border fires</i>

01:09.440 --> 01:12.080
<i># In the humming wires</i>

01:12.160 --> 01:16.320
<i># Hey man, you know
you're never coming back</i>

01:16.400 --> 01:19.920
<i># Past the square, past the bridge,
past the mills...</i>

01:20.000 --> 01:21.840
Shoot out his tyres.

01:23.480 --> 01:24.880
(SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

01:24.960 --> 01:26.400
And remember,

01:27.520 --> 01:29.760
I fire the final shot.

01:29.840 --> 01:33.880
<i># A tall handsome man
in a dusty black coat</i>

01:33.960 --> 01:37.080
<i># With a red right hand</i>

01:41.360 --> 01:43.960
<i># Red right hand</i>

01:46.680 --> 01:48.920
<i># Red right hand</i>

01:52.320 --> 01:53.320
<i># Red right hand #</i>

02:16.160 --> 02:17.560
Stay inside, love.

02:46.160 --> 02:47.360
Come on!

03:00.760 --> 03:01.760
Go! Go! Go!

03:05.240 --> 03:06.840
(SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

03:16.480 --> 03:17.680
LUCA: Come on.

03:31.280 --> 03:33.040
It's all right, love. It's all right.

03:33.120 --> 03:34.960
Come inside. Come inside. Come inside.

03:35.040 --> 03:37.560
Listen to me. Stay inside.
Don't come out.

04:08.280 --> 04:10.200
(GUNSHOTS)

04:43.760 --> 04:44.760
(DOOR OPENS)

04:46.400 --> 04:47.440
Get away from the window.

04:48.560 --> 04:50.560
Right. Stay inside.
Stay down.

04:59.600 --> 05:01.760
(BABY CRYING)

05:02.800 --> 05:04.680
Everyone, stay indoors!

05:04.760 --> 05:07.840
Stay down!
By order of the Peaky Blinders!

05:07.920 --> 05:09.200
Come on.

05:55.240 --> 05:56.360
(CLATTERING)

06:00.960 --> 06:02.560
Come here.

06:09.400 --> 06:10.560
(GASPS)

06:11.200 --> 06:14.040
Which way?
Which way did he go?

06:17.680 --> 06:19.080
You sure?

06:19.480 --> 06:20.800
Yeah?

06:36.360 --> 06:38.120
(PANTING)

06:49.560 --> 06:51.360
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

07:11.400 --> 07:13.360
-(GUNFIRE)
-(MAN GROANS)

07:13.720 --> 07:14.960
(SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

07:49.960 --> 07:51.400
Oi!

07:57.080 --> 07:58.880
(SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

08:11.400 --> 08:13.320
(GRUNTING)

08:19.800 --> 08:21.480
(SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

08:39.160 --> 08:40.960
(SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

08:45.320 --> 08:46.360
Hey!

08:47.160 --> 08:50.080
I know you own the cops
in this dirty fuckin' town!

08:51.160 --> 08:53.640
But you'll be dead
before they get here!

08:54.760 --> 08:57.000
Come on, me and you, Tommy.

08:59.040 --> 09:00.440
Come on.

09:10.200 --> 09:11.240
LUCA: Yeah.

09:14.080 --> 09:15.840
(IN ITALIAN)

09:41.200 --> 09:44.000
-(COMMOTION)
-Stop what you're doing!

10:02.760 --> 10:04.520
Enough!

10:05.520 --> 10:08.520
-(ALL SHOUTING)
-Get out of it!

10:08.960 --> 10:10.440
Get away!

10:10.920 --> 10:13.160
-Enough!
-What the fuck you doing here?

10:14.080 --> 10:16.720
Saving your life. All this.

10:17.400 --> 10:19.040
I'm a police officer, Tommy.

10:19.120 --> 10:21.480
I'm a fuckin' police officer, right?

10:21.560 --> 10:24.680
Doing my duty.
Stopping all this!

10:28.440 --> 10:30.880
Three bodies need cleaning up.

10:31.360 --> 10:33.200
No. Enough.

10:33.560 --> 10:36.480
Tell the people who live in these houses

10:36.560 --> 10:40.560
that they are free to go about
their lawful business!

10:40.640 --> 10:44.800
Tell them that the rule of law
has been restored!

10:45.640 --> 10:48.400
Haven't you heard, Tommy? Eh?

10:48.480 --> 10:50.120
Soldiers are coming.

11:24.440 --> 11:27.280
Do you know, I remember the very first
time you head-butted a policeman.

11:28.920 --> 11:32.080
After you got your OBE from the King,
I didn't think there'd be a next time.

11:41.080 --> 11:43.040
What do you think
you're gonna tell Arthur?

11:44.880 --> 11:46.320
I'll tell him the truth.

11:46.440 --> 11:47.560
(CLEARS THROAT)

11:50.840 --> 11:52.040
POLLY: They're here.

12:11.480 --> 12:12.560
ARTHUR: <i>So...</i>

12:15.600 --> 12:18.200
What the fuck happened today, Tom?

12:19.080 --> 12:22.160
We all heard,
shooting in Artillery Square.

12:22.240 --> 12:23.760
Yeah, there was.

12:24.800 --> 12:26.320
Today, I killed three men.

12:28.200 --> 12:29.920
Now our enemies will have to act.

12:33.200 --> 12:34.920
I suppose, they er...

12:35.640 --> 12:37.600
I suppose they took you
by surprise, did they?

12:37.680 --> 12:39.320
No, I knew they were coming.

12:42.040 --> 12:44.440
Just after Christmas,
I received a letter

12:45.160 --> 12:46.600
from Luca Changretta.

12:47.640 --> 12:50.680
Offering to spare my son,
if I gave up Tommy.

12:51.920 --> 12:53.320
And I gave Tommy up.

12:53.400 --> 12:55.960
Because that was the plan
that Polly and I agreed on.

12:56.760 --> 12:59.280
TOMMY: I knew that Luca,
would want to pull the trigger himself.

12:59.360 --> 13:00.480
(SNORTS)

13:00.560 --> 13:02.720
So I used the set-up as bait
to bring him in.

13:03.840 --> 13:05.480
You're a fuckin' idiot, Tom.

13:06.040 --> 13:08.520
Look, I didn't get Luca,
but I got three.

13:08.600 --> 13:11.280
All right? That's it.
That's what happened.

13:12.120 --> 13:13.840
-Come here, you.
-JOHNNY: Ah, but, he's right.

13:13.960 --> 13:17.400
I mean, I thought you'd gone soft.
(CHUCKLES)

13:17.680 --> 13:19.840
-So you got three?
-Yeah, I got three.

13:20.640 --> 13:23.080
Well, I'll drink to you, Tom.
You mad bastard.

13:23.240 --> 13:25.760
(LAUGHS)

13:26.280 --> 13:27.720
Hmm.

13:32.000 --> 13:36.280
Pretty soon, you're gonna get
the shakes. When your blood cools down.

13:37.040 --> 13:38.520
Let go get a drink.

13:38.600 --> 13:40.960
Dad, you got three what?

13:41.880 --> 13:45.480
I got three shillings on a
two shilling horse, my boy.

13:45.840 --> 13:47.480
TOMMY: You come with us, eh?

14:10.880 --> 14:12.600
(DOOR OPENS)

14:15.880 --> 14:17.400
Want a drink, Lizzie?

14:18.560 --> 14:20.080
I've had a hard day.

14:21.720 --> 14:23.920
I don't drink
whisky or gin any more, Tom.

14:24.520 --> 14:25.920
Why not?

14:28.120 --> 14:29.760
As they say, it harms the baby.

14:36.920 --> 14:39.440
Yes, it can only be yours.

14:40.080 --> 14:43.000
That day by the canal, when you were
fucking somebody else in your head.

14:44.560 --> 14:46.400
Except it wasn't her who got pregnant.

14:53.480 --> 14:54.680
Have a seat, Lizzie.

15:07.760 --> 15:09.320
(SIGHS)

15:09.400 --> 15:12.640
-All right, I know a woman, Lizzie.
-There are lots of woman, Tommy.

15:13.680 --> 15:16.000
If you don't know this already,
you don't know me.

15:16.720 --> 15:18.240
I'm keepin' it.

15:20.280 --> 15:22.160
Who's gonna run my fuckin' office?

15:25.440 --> 15:26.960
I'll find somebody.

15:28.720 --> 15:30.160
No.

15:32.000 --> 15:34.160
You better put a fuckin' advert
in the paper, then.

15:34.280 --> 15:35.960
I'm not laid up yet.

15:37.400 --> 15:39.920
You're not gonna work
with a child of mine inside of you.

15:43.920 --> 15:45.680
Fuck. Now my hand shakes.

15:48.280 --> 15:49.840
It's okay, Tom.

15:50.560 --> 15:52.120
We'll be okay.

15:55.040 --> 15:56.600
All this death, Lizzie...

15:58.160 --> 16:00.440
It'll be good to have some life, eh?

16:07.640 --> 16:09.280
I got three. (CLEARS THROAT)

16:10.800 --> 16:12.320
I know, Tom.

16:15.560 --> 16:17.440
One of them point-blank.

16:18.640 --> 16:21.640
A baby, little you and me.

16:25.160 --> 16:27.120
Point-blank, Lizzie.

16:29.680 --> 16:31.280
And he looked up at me.

16:38.080 --> 16:39.520
(CLEARS THROAT)

16:43.880 --> 16:47.720
You'll get an allowance,
every week from the company.

16:48.720 --> 16:50.360
Business is booming.

16:50.440 --> 16:52.880
We'll erm... Buy a nice house, eh?

16:55.600 --> 16:57.280
Come on, I'll drive you home.

17:37.360 --> 17:38.960
I'm just lookin'.

17:43.480 --> 17:44.480
(GLASS BREAKING)

18:00.520 --> 18:01.960
(SNORTS)

18:03.200 --> 18:04.680
(SNIFFS)

18:08.360 --> 18:10.120
(OPENS BOTTLE)

18:17.440 --> 18:18.600
Hmm?

18:34.720 --> 18:36.000
(DOOR OPENS)

18:37.080 --> 18:38.560
-Fuck.
-Linda.

18:38.640 --> 18:40.880
-Arthur, you scared me to death.
-Linda!

18:42.440 --> 18:43.720
(GROANS)

18:45.560 --> 18:48.760
Linda, I need you to save me.
I'm dying.

18:48.840 --> 18:50.920
You're drunk. Again.

18:51.000 --> 18:53.200
I'm drunk again.

18:54.400 --> 18:56.200
I am drunk again.

18:58.280 --> 19:00.160
I need you to save me.

19:02.200 --> 19:04.880
Tell me what you said to me
this morning.

19:05.240 --> 19:07.560
Tell me... Tell me again.

19:07.880 --> 19:09.400
Tell me.

19:09.680 --> 19:12.440
Say it, say it, say it. Tell me.

19:13.360 --> 19:15.840
We'll be back in our garden

19:17.000 --> 19:20.160
before the time comes to plant
anything out.

19:21.640 --> 19:23.400
Just one winter.

19:24.480 --> 19:26.080
(GROGGILY) Just one winter.

19:33.080 --> 19:34.360
Come to bed, Arthur.

19:38.760 --> 19:39.840
(GRUNTS)

19:41.240 --> 19:42.800
They're coming, boys.

20:10.160 --> 20:11.600
MICHAEL: No.

20:13.000 --> 20:14.440
No fucking way.

20:14.720 --> 20:16.680
You've never eaten hedgehog, Michael?

20:18.320 --> 20:19.920
I'm getting back in this car.

20:20.000 --> 20:23.360
Michael, you're number two
on Luca Changretta's hit list.

20:23.520 --> 20:25.200
Yeah, and I'll stay in a hotel.

20:25.280 --> 20:28.320
If you stay in a hotel,
I'll know where you are.

20:28.400 --> 20:29.920
So will the people who take you there.

20:30.000 --> 20:31.920
So will the people
who work in the hotel.

20:32.120 --> 20:34.320
And hotels don't move around.

20:35.240 --> 20:37.400
They don't even know
where they'll be tomorrow.

20:37.480 --> 20:39.480
They follow the patron and the crows.

20:39.560 --> 20:41.600
And if anyone
should come for you, Michael,

20:42.320 --> 20:45.200
the Palmers and the Boswells
will put up a fair fight.

20:48.040 --> 20:49.480
Take your medicine.

20:51.000 --> 20:53.200
-I'll take them.
-Pain killers.

20:53.880 --> 20:56.840
The hills up there,
they'll heal you much quicker.

20:58.200 --> 20:59.760
Fuckin' witches,
the lot of them.

21:00.480 --> 21:02.480
Show some respect, Mr Gray.

21:03.000 --> 21:05.240
They've agreed to welcome you
on account of your blood.

21:12.560 --> 21:14.040
Take your medicine.

21:15.080 --> 21:16.360
Take the gun.

21:17.640 --> 21:19.360
I won't be able to contact you,

21:19.960 --> 21:21.360
till you phone me.

21:22.800 --> 21:24.120
We'll make a plan.

21:27.400 --> 21:29.280
Tommy says it won't be long.

21:30.760 --> 21:32.280
Then we'll be free.

21:40.520 --> 21:42.440
You might learn something.

21:44.800 --> 21:48.440
Tell them your grandmother
was a Gypsy princess.

21:48.960 --> 21:50.840
Name of Birdy Boswell.

21:51.720 --> 21:54.080
You're royalty up there, Michael.

22:08.360 --> 22:10.000
ABERAMA:
Is that true, Mrs Gray?

22:11.400 --> 22:12.560
What?

22:13.600 --> 22:15.160
Don't I look like royalty?

22:15.240 --> 22:17.120
Well, now that you mention it, you do.

22:24.680 --> 22:27.040
I've been cooped up
in Small Heath too long.

22:30.000 --> 22:32.000
I can smell spring in the air.

22:37.280 --> 22:39.160
Do you know
a longer way back, Mr Gold?

22:42.680 --> 22:45.680
I know ways back,
would take forever.

22:46.480 --> 22:47.920
Get in, Your Majesty.

23:00.760 --> 23:05.800
<i># When your work is over</i>

23:07.360 --> 23:10.400
<i># Your day is done</i>

23:12.080 --> 23:14.720
<i># Put down your hammer... #</i>

23:14.800 --> 23:17.120
I thought you were a busy woman.

23:17.400 --> 23:19.680
<i># Into my world come #</i>

23:19.760 --> 23:20.960
Do you have time for this?

23:21.760 --> 23:23.720
-Is it a buck?
-It is a buck.

23:25.040 --> 23:27.920
Good, bucks taste better.

23:37.120 --> 23:39.360
In this smoke, I'm 16 again.

23:43.120 --> 23:45.880
When the police were after my dad,
he used to take us out.

23:46.280 --> 23:48.480
We'd be gone for days living on
what he caught.

23:51.000 --> 23:53.800
Oh... Do you have a sharp knife?

24:05.880 --> 24:07.800
I heard you have second sight.

24:10.680 --> 24:12.760
I heard that you speak with the dead.

24:14.760 --> 24:16.080
Yes.

24:20.880 --> 24:22.640
Your wife's often around you.

24:23.520 --> 24:24.880
She watches you.

24:27.160 --> 24:28.680
Is she watching me now?

24:35.880 --> 24:36.960
POLLY: No.

24:41.520 --> 24:43.160
Your family were healers?

24:43.840 --> 24:45.320
Yeah, long time ago.

24:48.840 --> 24:51.040
Came back
when I put my head in a noose.

24:54.280 --> 24:57.480
It's like putting your head through
a window and seeing the whole world.

25:00.840 --> 25:01.920
Give me the rabbit.

25:04.120 --> 25:05.440
And the knife.

25:10.200 --> 25:11.560
You know, Polly...

25:13.360 --> 25:18.520
I believe it's you who's kept
Tommy Shelby alive all these years.

25:18.800 --> 25:20.800
How we've kept each other alive...

25:23.880 --> 25:26.320
That I didn't just put my head
through that window.

25:28.440 --> 25:30.160
I climbed through it.

25:31.960 --> 25:34.800
First, I thought it was madness,
but, no.

25:35.960 --> 25:38.200
When you put your head
out of that window,

25:39.640 --> 25:42.320
you can do anything you want.

25:43.960 --> 25:45.800
'Cause there are no rules.

25:48.640 --> 25:50.480
'Cause there are no risks.

25:56.120 --> 25:57.960
Now, give me the knife.

26:15.800 --> 26:17.160
Now, come here.

26:23.280 --> 26:25.040
I can do whatever I want

26:26.360 --> 26:28.320
whenever the mood takes me.

26:29.880 --> 26:32.160
And you are a strong handsome man.

26:33.640 --> 26:36.440
And this is a beautiful place
in the world.

26:38.040 --> 26:39.520
And it is.

26:40.600 --> 26:42.000
This time.

26:55.960 --> 26:58.280
Let me make one thing clear, Mr Gold.

26:59.040 --> 27:00.560
I just gave Michael a little speech

27:00.640 --> 27:02.840
about how no one would know
where to find him.

27:04.000 --> 27:05.760
But you'd know how to get him.

27:06.680 --> 27:08.920
If any harm comes to Michael,

27:09.000 --> 27:11.120
you shall have me as your enemy.

27:12.400 --> 27:15.240
And none of your knives can kill me.

27:18.600 --> 27:20.000
Do you understand?

27:20.640 --> 27:22.280
Oh, I understand.

27:25.240 --> 27:26.960
(SPEAKING IN ROMANI)

27:54.760 --> 27:56.840
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

28:22.760 --> 28:24.200
Mr Solomons.

28:24.600 --> 28:25.800
Mmm.

28:27.560 --> 28:29.600
My little cousin was born blind.

28:30.720 --> 28:35.800
As a result, I now donate
a considerable sum of money to a charity

28:35.880 --> 28:40.000
which gives dogs with eyes
to blind Jews.

28:41.680 --> 28:44.280
The chairman of the board recommends

28:44.360 --> 28:48.440
that those of us who were blessed
with the gift of sight,

28:48.520 --> 28:52.560
and that we spend, you know,
at least half an hour a day

28:52.640 --> 28:55.040
with our eyes closed
so that we may

28:55.120 --> 28:57.640
that we may better understand the...

28:58.680 --> 29:01.400
Well, the darkness, and erm...

29:02.040 --> 29:05.400
Also, to increase
our donations and that. Mmm.

29:07.120 --> 29:08.320
What time is it?

29:11.960 --> 29:13.440
Twenty-nine minutes past eight.

29:13.760 --> 29:15.280
Right. Well, then I...

29:15.360 --> 29:18.640
I have another minute to go,
actually, but you er...

29:20.080 --> 29:21.680
You can begin. Go on.

29:32.760 --> 29:34.800
I'm Luca Changretta.

29:35.080 --> 29:37.400
Oh, yeah, I know who you are. Mmm.

29:37.560 --> 29:39.640
You are a bit of a failure, aren't you?

29:39.720 --> 29:42.480
You come all the way over here
to this country,

29:42.560 --> 29:45.320
in order to
kill Tommy Shelby,

29:45.400 --> 29:47.440
but, I mean... (CHUCKLES)

29:48.360 --> 29:50.280
Well, he's not dead, is he? So...

29:50.360 --> 29:51.920
-No.
-No.

29:52.040 --> 29:53.160
He ain't.

29:54.200 --> 29:56.560
How much time have I got left, mate?

29:59.200 --> 30:00.360
Ten seconds.

30:00.800 --> 30:02.120
Nine seconds.

30:02.200 --> 30:03.520
Eight seconds.

30:04.400 --> 30:05.760
Five.

30:06.160 --> 30:07.520
Four.

30:07.720 --> 30:08.960
Three.

30:09.400 --> 30:10.680
Two.

30:10.920 --> 30:12.120
One.

30:13.640 --> 30:15.280
Right. Hello.

30:17.480 --> 30:19.080
How can I help you?

30:22.560 --> 30:25.000
-I have a proposition for you.
-Mmm. No, it's...

30:25.080 --> 30:28.360
I already know
what do you want.

30:28.440 --> 30:31.600
Yeah? I just want to
hear you say it out loud

30:31.680 --> 30:34.760
so that I can check
how ridiculous it is.

30:35.040 --> 30:37.280
(SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

30:48.080 --> 30:50.520
I hear there's gonna be a little fight.

30:50.600 --> 30:55.120
A boxing match between your boy
and Tommy Shelby's boy.

30:55.720 --> 30:58.080
-Eh? Birmingham.
-Mmm-hmm.

30:58.160 --> 31:00.440
And the whole Shelby family
is gonna be there.

31:00.520 --> 31:01.960
Hmm.

31:02.320 --> 31:05.160
And you, Mr Solomons,

31:05.520 --> 31:07.400
you too will be there.

31:08.520 --> 31:10.640
-Huh?
-Er, that's it.

31:10.920 --> 31:12.800
I'll tell you what, all right?

31:13.120 --> 31:15.600
Here's a gift. It's free.

31:15.680 --> 31:17.920
A souvenir of your visit here.

31:18.000 --> 31:21.560
Goodbye. Trot on.
Down there is Bonny Street.

31:25.440 --> 31:27.000
(SNIFFS)

31:28.920 --> 31:31.120
You know, they say you're a smart guy.

31:31.720 --> 31:35.680
(CHUCKLES) I mean, you already know
what we want before we say it.

31:37.600 --> 31:42.800
That's funny 'cause now I believe
I know what you want

31:42.880 --> 31:45.840
-even before you say it.
-Mmm? Mmm.

